Dear Mr. Salvador,

Thank you for your email of today inviting my views on the Defendants=E2=80=99 N2=
44 application seeking an extension of time to file their Acknowledgment of =
Service and Summary Grounds of Resistance.

I understand that the Defendants=E2=80=99 application sought an extension until 1=
2 January 2026, and that their Acknowledgment of Service and Summary Grounds=
 have now been filed. I recognise that the Court is therefore considering wh=
ether to regularise the position retrospectively.

I do not oppose the Court granting the extension for the purpose of regular=
ising the record.

However, I do not accept the Defendants=E2=80=99 assertion in their application t=
hat there is =E2=80=9Cno urgency=E2=80=9D or that the extension has caused no prejudice.=
 As set out in my pleadings, this claim concerns ongoing issues of disabilit=
y participation, subsistence, and procedural fairness, and delay has had a m=
aterial impact on my ability to participate effectively as a disabled litiga=
nt in person.

I therefore ask that, if the extension is granted, it be on the basis that =
no finding is made that there has been no prejudice or urgency, and that my =
position in that regard is preserved.

Yours faithfully,

Nadia Zahmoul
Claimant (Litigant in Person)

=20

